summary: Yoongi and Taehyung - They find out that they’re infertile Warning - May be upsetting to some readers You hold your husband’s...
body:
Yoongi and Taehyung - They find out that they’re infertile

Warning - May be upsetting to some readers

You hold your husband’s hands tightly as the doctor shuffles through the papers on her desk. The two of you have been trying to have a baby for a long time now, but you haven’t gotten pregnant. He’s actually the one who suggested going to a clinic, just to test that everything is okay. You were sure that everything is fine, but the saddened look on the doctor’s face says differently,

“I’m very sorry, but you’re infertile. The two of you will not be able to conceive naturally,” The doctor says to your husband, smiling gently, “But there are a few other options that the two of you can look into if you really want children. Not that this is the time. I can arrange an appointment for the two of you in a week, but that is all for today,” She continues, and you thank her graciously. You stand up to shake her hand as she leaves the two of you in the office for a moment, but your husband can’t make himself move.

Yoongi

“Do the tests again,” Yoongi mumbles at the last second. The doctor has just put her hand on the door knob, but the sound of Yoongi’s gruff voice makes her stop short. You sit down in front of your husband and ask what he meant, “I mean, do the tests again!” He demands, standing up to stare the doctor down, “You must be wrong, there’s nothing wrong with me! Do the tests again,” Your heart breaks to look at Yoongi like this. He’s not shouting, but you can hear the desperation in his voice,

“Yoongi, there is nothing wrong with you,” You say quietly, moving to stand in front of him. You take his hands again, drawing his attention back to you so that the doctor can slip out unnoticed. Yoongi can seem very intimidating to others, even though you know he’s actually a cupcake inside, “I love you so much, and I know that we can move past this. It doesn’t matter if you’re infertile, that doesn’t even mean anything. We’ll find another way,” You tell him, searching his eyes for the pain you know he’s hiding behind this aggression,

“I don’t want to find another way, though,” Yoongi says, voice breaking slightly. There’s the pain. He feels like it’s squeezing his chest and stopping him from breathing. He feels like a fish out of water, “I don’t want another way, I want this way,” His voice begins to trail off as tears fight to be seen. His eyes flicker down from yours, and your heart breaks even further. You’ve never seen Yoongi like this before.

Taehyung

Taehyung can’t bring himself to move for a very long time. He ca actually feel all of his life dreams come crashing down around him. All he’s ever really wanted was to be a father to 3… 4… 5… however many kids he could have. He could so clearly see you laid in a hospital bed, a beautiful baby in your arms with their older brothers and sisters squirming around beside you to get a look. That’s gone now, and even though there may be other ways to have that, it feels to Taehyung that it’s all gone,

“I’m so sorry, Tae,” You whisper, rubbing his arm comfortingly. You know how badly he wanted this, and for it to be a problem on his side of things? This must be devastating. It’s not easy for you either, knowing the two of you will never be able to have little versions of the two of you waddling around, laughing and teasing, hurts. But for now, the biggest problem is the fact that Taehyung isn’t moving. The only sign of life are the fat tears rolling down his face, “Taehyung, baby, talk to me,” You plead, and Taehyung shakes his head slowly as if to clear his mind,

“This is all my fault. It’s a problem with me, and it is my issue. I’m sorry that I’ve done this to you. I know you wanted kids as well,” He says, his tone more melancholic than you’ve ever heard. It hurts to hear him blame himself like this, but you can’t even interject and tell him that it’s okay before he’s standing up, not quite meeting your gaze, “I think we should have some time to ourselves for a while. Figure out what’s right for us as individuals,” He looks like he’s going to say something else, but gives up and lets himself out. You’re left alone, trying to process everything that just happened in the space of a few minutes.

Masterlist

summary: Symphony of the Black Keys
title: Symphony of the Black Keys
body:
by placeakaponit

Min Yoongi goes to New York City, thinking that someone would immediately scout him as he was one of the best pianists Korea. After a few months of gaining little to no attention and being constantly ignored, he begins to lose hope in the big city. But in the midst of his cloudy ambitions, the sun had finally appeared in his life.

Life’s like a piano, there are white and black keys symbolizing the good and the bad experiences respectively.

Yoongi wondered what key would Jung Hoseok fall into in his life.
